race.comment: SHE'S BRUTAL (8) stepped up to this trip beaten 1.4L off a near miss at Ipswich. Should be at peak now and looks well-placed to go on with the job. TICKLE MY TOSEN (3) presents fourth up and was tracking well before a plain run here. May have had an excuse and the blinkers go back on. Draws an inside gate today and can improve into the finish. BROOKLYN DAISY (1) has five placings from six outings this preparation, finishing 1.3L adrift at the Sunshine Coast her most recent. Has a handy 2kg claim, but the outside barrier needs to be managed. LECAN (7) hasn't been far away since the Maiden win three runs back. Just missed at Gatton last time and maps for a soft run. In good hands and must be respected. NIENNA (9) was backed off the map when winning her Maiden here over a bit longer and can build on that.
